grub configuration can be found in
 
[1] /etc/grub.d/ or 
[2] /etc/default/grub

amd grub.conf file

[*] /boot/grub/grub.cfg

to generate this file we have commands which are 

If we make any change in grub file we will have to make it in either of two above given location.
And then use [$ sudo grub-mkconfig or grub2-mkconfig ] -o filename.cfg
And then this config file to /boot/grub/
create a backup of original file then use grub-install 
and then we have to something in grub menu
